1.The code is mainly running on Windows 10.
2.The R version is 3.2.3.
3.The libraries we are going to use are:
  (1) EBImage
       Use the following code to install the EBImage 
       ###
       source("http://bioconductor.org/biocLite.R")
       biocLite()
       biocLite("EBImage")
       library("EBImage")
       ###
       If you meet any problem, please run R as the administor.
  (2) gbm
      It can be installed from tools-install packages and then install from CRAN 
  (3) randomForest
      It can be installed from tools-install packages and then install from CRAN 
